    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCannot cover the first **screen** line with a float window assuming that it is configured with `relative = 'win'` and non-empty `bufpos`:\r\n\r\n![nvim](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/11404453/1a853bc6-0cb1-4fad-9a96-f869659e7a5a)\r\n\r\nI did not found such issue both open and closed. Please close this issue if it's not a bug or if a duplicate exists. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\r\nvim.wo.number = true\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, true, {'', '', '', ''})\r\nvim.bo[0].buftype = 'nofile'\r\nlocal winId = nil\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_feedkeys(vim.keycode('<C-e>'), 'n', false)\r\n\r\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\n\r\nlocal function test()\r\n  if winId then\r\n    vim.api.nvim_win_close(winId, true)\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  local bufline = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)[1]\r\n  local winConfig = {\r\n    relative = 'win',\r\n    width = 10,\r\n    height = 1,\r\n    style = 'minimal',\r\n    bufpos = { bufline - 2, 0 },\r\n  }\r\n  winId = vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf, false, winConfig)\r\nend\r\n\r\ntest()\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('CursorMoved', {callback = test})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe first screen line is covered with the float window in the same way as lines below. \n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0fe0cf5adaab06b92250eb350306de63c4d4f36f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n-\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.26.5-5, tmux 3.3a-5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
